places = ['switzerland', 'london', 'melbourne', 'new zealand', 'canada']

#print your list in its original order
print('Here is the original list: ')
print(places)

print("\nAlphabetical:")
places.sort()
print(places)

print("\nOriginal order:")
print(places)

print("\nReverse alphabetical:")
places.sort(reverse = True)
print(places)

print("\nOriginal order:")
print(places)

print("\nReverse:")
places.reverse()
print(places)

print("\nReverse again:")
places.reverse()
print(places)

print("\nAlphabetical")
places.sort()
print(places)

print("\nReverse alphabetical")
places.sort(reverse = True)
print(places)

import math
a = int(input("Please enter a: "))
b = int(input("Please enter b: "))

#the sum of a and b 
sum = a + b
print("The sum of a and b is {}".format(sum))

#the difference when b is subtracted from a
difference = a - b
print("The difference when b is subtracted from a is {}".format(difference))

#the product of a and b
product = a * b
print("The product of a and b is {}".format(product))

#the quotient when a is divided by b
quotient = a / b
print("The product when a is divided by b is {:.2f}".format(quotient))

#the remainder when a is divided by b
remainder = a % b
print("The remainder when a is divided by b is {}".format(remainder))

#the result of log10 a
result1 = math.log10(a)
print("The result of log10 a is {:.2f}".format(result1))

#the result of ab
result2 = a ** b
print("The result of a^b is {}".format(result2))

Please enter b: 2

The difference when b is subtracted from a is 22
The product of a and b is 48
The product when a is divided by b is 12.00
The remainder when a is divided by b is 0
The result of log10 a is 1.38
The result of ab is 576

math.pi

radius = float(input("Please enter a radius: "))

print('The volume of a sphere with radius {:.0f} is {:.2f}'.format(radius, volume_of_sphere))

Out[93]:
False

FALSE: 0.1 - kiểu float - một cách biểu diễn xấp xỉ cho một số thực bất kì nào đó

  • ví dụ: 0.0000000000000089
  • Mặc dù việc xấp xỉ (làm tròn) này không đáng kể nhưng khi cộng nhiều giá trị như vậy lại sẽ dẫn đến một sai số lớn

In [42]:
#Let A be the event of choosing 1 from the list 1
#Let B be the event of choosing 1 from the list 2

list1 = list("10101000100101101010")
list2 = list("101110010110101000001010")

#count the number of "1" in the list 1
count1 = list1.count('1')
print('The number of "1" in the list 1 is: {}'.format(count1))

#count the number of "0" in the list2
count2 = list2.count('0')
print('The number of "0" in the list 2 is: {}'.format(count2))

#calculate the probability P(A)
prob_of_eventA = count1 / len(list1)
print('The probability P(A) is {}'.format(prob_of_eventA))

#calculate the probability P(B)
prob_of_eventB = 1 - (count2 / len(list2))
print('The probability P(B) is {}'.format(prob_of_eventB))

#calculate the probability P(A, B)
prob1 = prob_of_eventA * prob_of_eventB
print('The probability P(A, B) is {}'.format(prob1))

#calculate the probability P(A | not B)
prob2= prob_of_eventA
print('The probability P(A | not B) is {}'.format(prob2))

The number of "1" in the list 1 is: 9
The number of "0" in the list 2 is: 13
The probability P(A) is 0.45
The probability P(B) is 0.45833333333333337
The probability P(A, B) is 0.20625000000000002
The probability P(A | not B) is 0.45
